arStrings.szText: I’ve been struggling with something. In Hell...when we didn’t know who to use the soulstone on, why did you ask me to choose?
Between Lilith in my veins, and Mephisto in my ears, I couldn’t trust myself.
But you could trust me? A-a grieving child. I got stuck! I messed it all up.
...I was our group’s fist. Killing is my trade. Donan was our stone mage. Lorath, our leader.
And you...you were our compass. Always looking north, to Sanctuary and her future. Weighed by burdens, but not swayed by them.
I’m sorry, for putting that on you. But I don’t regret it. Despite Mephisto’s best efforts, you are still you. That alone is proof I didn’t choose wrong.
...You think too highly of me. Next time, we choose together. All right, friend?
Come on. They’re waiting for us in the council room.
